Callisto is the second largest moon in the Jupiter system and is nearly the size of Mercury. It is the most distant of the Galilean moons from Jupiter. It was discovered in 1610 by Galileo Galilei and independently observed by Simon Marius.Sources:Image – http://photojournal.jpl.nasa.gov/catalog/PIA03456Profile – http://solarsystem.nasa.gov/planets/io, http://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/planetary/factsheet/joviansatfact.html